FBIS4-3989 "drchi082_a_94018" FBIS-CHI-94-082 Daily Report 26 Apr 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General Ji Chaozhu To Represent UN at Nixon's Funeral Ji Chaozhu To Represent UN at Nixon's Funeral OW2604203894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1957 GMT 26 Apr 94 OW2604203894 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] United Nations, April 26 (XINHUA) -- Ji Chaozhu, U.N. under-secretary-general in charge of the Department for Development, Support and Management Services, will represent the United Nations at former U.S. President Richard Nixon's funeral on Wednesday [27 April]. Ji, a national of China, was the senior interpreter for the top Chinese leaders when Nixon was in China for his historical visit to the People's Republic. Nixon, President of the United States from 1969 to 1974, died last Friday. His remains were flown to his birthplace Yorba Linda, California, on Tuesday for the funeral.
